00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:42.192
Here's what we're going
to try, boiling water,

00:00:42.200 --> 00:00:43.100
letting it cool down,

00:00:43.100 --> 00:00:46.800
and then boiling it again is
one that I've seen all over the place

00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:49.400
as a sure fire method
for making clear ice.

00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:51.920
Then there's the idea
that you can use distilled water,

00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:55.400
and it's complete lack of impurities
will let the water crystallize

00:00:55.400 --> 00:00:57.300
into a nice clear formation.

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:00.800
We're also going to try putting
some water in our vacuum chamber,

00:01:00.800 --> 00:01:02.600
and letting that run
for a while to sort

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:05.300
of suck out any extra dissolved gases.

00:01:05.300 --> 00:01:07.540
Hopefully, those won't
get trapped in the ice,

00:01:07.540 --> 00:01:09.440
and that will let us get a clear result.

00:01:09.440 --> 00:01:13.200
Then finally, we have a small cooler,
and we're just going to fill this most

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:16.100
of the way with water,
and put this freezer as well,

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:18.400
and see what happens
if we force all of the water

00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:19.820
to freeze from one direction,

00:01:19.820 --> 00:01:22.000
in this case, it will freeze
from the top down.

00:01:22.440 --> 00:01:24.880
As a first step, let's fill
our small pot with water.

00:01:24.952 --> 00:01:25.860
We'll boil it,

00:01:25.860 --> 00:01:27.860
let it cool down back to room temperature,

00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:30.920
and then boil it a second time
before pouring it into this container,

00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:31.840
where will freeze it.

00:01:31.840 --> 00:01:38.360
[Music]

00:01:38.360 --> 00:01:40.080
This one's just
distilled water.

00:01:40.582 --> 00:01:43.722
Distilled water is water that's been
run through a distilling process.

00:01:43.722 --> 00:01:47.320
It's boiled off and the steam is
condensed back down into water,

00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:51.000
