is water that's completely sterile,

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:52.100
and has nothing else in it.

00:01:52.100 --> 00:01:54.900
So this should just be hydrogen
and oxygen atoms

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:56.780
bonded together in water form.

00:01:56.780 --> 00:01:57.780
Nothing else.

00:01:57.780 --> 00:02:16.620
[Music]

00:02:16.620 --> 00:02:17.140
Okay.

00:02:17.140 --> 00:02:20.000
Now, we've got some normal
tap water in one of our containers,

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:21.972
and we're going to vacuum it.

00:02:23.712 --> 00:02:25.600
Not with a vacuum cleaner,
vacuum chamber.

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:29.000
We hit a low pressure.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:30.900
That's about 25
inches of mercury.

00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:34.700
It starts boiling and bubbling,
and the idea is that by putting it

00:02:34.700 --> 00:02:38.400
in a vacuum chamber,
all of the extra dissolved gases

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:39.760
get pulled right out.

00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:42.700
I'm not entirely sure how
that's supposed to work,

00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:48.842
because we are obviously just creating gas
by causing it to boil at a low pressure.

00:02:49.572 --> 00:02:51.700
There could be a level
where it pulls out gases

00:02:51.700 --> 00:02:53.180
before adding more in.

00:02:55.740 --> 00:02:58.400
Okay, I think our water
is good and vacuumed.

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:08.680
[Music]

00:03:08.680 --> 00:03:11.740
Now, let's take our cooler,
and fill it most of the way.

00:03:11.740 --> 00:03:13.620
We'll put that in the freezer,
