00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:47.680
[Music]

00:09:47.680 --> 00:09:50.900
Having melted and chipped away most
of the white portion of the ice,

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:53.500
you can see how clear we are this point.

00:09:56.440 --> 00:09:59.200
Let's just set it down here,
and look through it like that.

00:10:00.362 --> 00:10:03.500
Obviously, there are still
some little bubbles in here,

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:06.240
and if you wanted to make sure
you didn't have any of those,

00:10:06.300 --> 00:10:07.600
there's a few things I'd recommend.

00:10:07.600 --> 00:10:10.100
First is actually taking
the ice out sooner.

00:10:10.100 --> 00:10:15.500
Don't let it freeze all the way through,
but just have it freeze for the top inch

00:10:15.500 --> 00:10:16.200
and a half or so,

00:10:16.200 --> 00:10:18.400
and then take the cooler out,
take your ice block out

00:10:18.400 --> 00:10:19.640
and use it however you like.

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:22.960
The way that I've done it
is just to demonstrate why

00:10:22.962 --> 00:10:24.200
we get bubbles in the ice.

00:10:24.200 --> 00:10:26.900
We get bubbles in the ice
because there is gas

00:10:26.900 --> 00:10:28.982
trapped in the water,
and we can't get that out

00:10:28.982 --> 00:10:32.020
by boiling it or by vacuum chambering it,

00:10:32.020 --> 00:10:35.500
but it's going to have gas
and contaminants in the water even

00:10:35.500 --> 00:10:38.100
if we use distilled water,
vacuum it, boil it, all of that.

00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:42.200
But if we freeze it from only
one direction, then they all

00:10:42.200 --> 00:10:43.500
sort of get pushed out of the way,

00:10:43.500 --> 00:10:46.500
and we get some nice,
beautifully clear ice

00:10:46.500 --> 00:10:49.900
before we get to the portions
that are going to cause problems.

00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:52.260
Before we get to the bubbles and stuff,

00:10:52.260 --> 00:10:54.120
and then those will get
pushed to the bottom.

00:10:54.120 --> 00:10:57.400
So this is the only way that
I have found to freeze

00:10:57.400 --> 00:10:58.500
clear ice at home.

